gomodel:SYNGO_194  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Rab4B was detected by mass spectrometry on highly purified synaptic vesicles. This was further validated using anti-Rab4 antibody by immunoblotting and by staining of GFP-Rab4B with synaptophysin in transiently transfected hippocampal neurons. The presence of Rab4B in synaptic vesicles was separately identified in another study (Takamori et al., 2006; PMID 17110340) by mass spectrometry.. Experimental description: Legend to Figure 2 \"Enrichment profiles of Rab GTPases on purified SVs isolated from rat brain homogenates, determined by quantitative immunoblotting.\"\n\n20/2/2017 Pim:\nSpecies of Rab4B OE construct used in Fig.3 is not stated in the M&M. Table 1 and Fig.2 are sufficient to claim the selected term, however, and species is set to Rat." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0098993 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_194" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

